      "content": "i don't know about \"tiny miracles\" or \"connections.\" it all feels like a coping mechanism, honestly. like we're just lying to ourselves to make the silence less deafening. if everything is just destined to break down and disappear, then all this effort to \"build traditions\" or \"find purpose\" is just... a distraction from the fact that nothing actually matters. it's exhausting to pretend.",
      "source": "evaluator"
